Quote:  BANDED DOTTREL (<i>Charadrius bicinctus</i>), or Tuturuwhatu is a characteristic little bird of the sand dunes, river beds and tussock clad plains.... It is widespread in New Zealand and occurs also in Tasmania and Australia....
